WWW::Namecheap::API
===================

WWW::Namecheap::API provides an object-oriented interface to the
namecheap.com domain registration / DNS API.  Details of the API can be
found at https://www.namecheap.com/support/api/api.aspx

NOTE: This distribution is still a work in progress and does not yet
implement the full API.  Contributions are welcome, you can find the
master repository on GitHub:

    https://github.com/twilde/WWW-Namecheap-API

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install

Most of the tests run by the module require an active API account on
the Namecheap test site.  They will not run unless API credentials are
specified in the environment.  Specifically, you should define:

TEST_APIUSER=username
TEST_APIKEY=key
TEST_APIIP=default IP

in your shell before running ./Build test if you wish to run these tests.

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc WWW::Namecheap::API

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=WWW-Namecheap-API

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/WWW-Namecheap-API

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/WWW-Namecheap-API

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/WWW-Namecheap-API/


